==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pyemia
<hw>Py*e"mi*a</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ pus + <?/
blood.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A form of blood poisoning produced
by the absorption of pyogenic microorganisms into the blood, usually
from a wound or local inflammation. It is characterized by multiple
abscesses throughout the body, and is attended with irregularly
recurring chills, fever, profuse sweating, and exhaustion.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Py*⟦ae⟧"mic</wf>, <wf>Py*e"mic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

